# **CASTING CALL!!!**

We are casting for a new tour of the children‚Äôs theatre show, ‚ÄúTom Gates Live‚Äù, based on the popular book series by Liz Pichon.

The show is written and directed by Miranda Larson with songs and music by Barrie Bignold and is produced by Mark Thompson at MT Productions.

Rehearsals begin on 19th January ‚Äì 29th January 2025 in London.
Tour dates Jan ‚Äì Oct 2026. We are currently have 65 tour dates and counting. 

# **ROLE: Tom Gates**

Tom Gates is an easily distracted and creative 10-year-old boy who loves doodling, listening to music, and annoying his older sister, Delia.

He is best friends with Derek, and they share a passion for music, with dreams of becoming rock stars in their band, DogZombies.

We are looking for a musical theatre performer that can sing, perform slapstick and comedy, and can perform the role of a young boy.

Within the show, there is basic singing, dancing and movement but nothing too technical.

 

The successful applicant will need to be comfortable assisting with the load ins/ outs and have a full UK drivers licence as they will be asked to assist driving the touring van

Playing age: 16 years - 23 years

Gender: Male

**Contract info:**

Rehearsal fee: ¬£550pw

Show day fee: ¬£150

Travel day fee: ¬£50

Subsistence: ¬£20

Please send cv's and headshots to casting.mtproductions@gmail.com

items.text:
Altarena Playhouse (Alameda, CA) is holding auditions for *‚ÄòNight Mother *by Marsha Norman, Directed by ShawnJ West

 

Performance Dates: May 29th through June 28th     

(Fridays/Saturdays at 7:30 pm, and Sundays at 2:00 pm)

 

SHOW SYNOPSIS:

Thelma Cates is a mother and widow who lives with her daughter, Jessie. Jessie is the divorced mother of a troubled son who struggles with life as an unemployed epileptic. She confesses to her mother that she is going to take her life. Tonight. As Mama pleads with her to reconsider her decision, old secrets are revealed, and long-ignored feelings rise to the surface. The mother-daughter bond between Jessie and Mama becomes stronger and lovelier than ever, making it possible for Jessie to end her noisy, cluttered existence, and take a quieter, calmer path with closure and love.

 

AUDITION DATES:

Monday, January 19th at 7:00pm and Saturday, January 24th at 1:00pm, by appointment

 

Callbacks: Monday, February 2nd, 7-10 pm, by invitation

 

Rehearsals begin April 25, 2026 at 11:00 am

 

Auditions will be held at the Altarena Playhouse, 1409 High Street, Alameda

 

Performers of all races, ethnicities, and genders are encouraged to audition.

 

Non-AEA only. $500 Reimbursement for expenses

 

 

CHARACTER DESCRIPTIONS:

THELMA ‚ÄúMAMA‚Äù CATES (Female, 60s)

Warm, talkative, and steeped in the routines of her home life, Thelma is a woman who uses chatter, caretaking, and small comforts to keep the world steady. Beneath her practical exterior, she carries deep anxieties, regrets, and unspoken guilt that surface as the night unfolds. Actors should bring emotional dexterity, humor grounded in truth, and the ability to navigate sharp tonal shifts as Mama confronts an unthinkable situation with both denial and fierce love.

 

JESSIE CATES (Female, 40s)

Direct, methodical, and emotionally contained, Jessie is a woman who has lived with chronic illness, disappointment, and a profound sense of futility. She speaks plainly and acts with quiet determination, revealing a grounded pragmatism rather than melodrama. Actors should bring a nuanced stillness, clarity of intention, and the ability to reveal the powerful internal life beneath Jessie‚Äôs calm, steady presence.

 

To sign up and for audition sides, visit:  [https://www.signupgenius.com/go/9040F4FAFAB28A2F94-61249455-night](https://www.signupgenius.com/go/9040F4FAFAB28A2F94-61249455-night)

 

Please contact Katina at [artisticdirector@altarena.org](mailto:artisticdirector@altarena.org) should you have any questions.

Vicky Boone Casting is looking for a real Latino or Latino-Mixed family for background roles in an Academy Sports commercial. 
Details below:

Project: Academy Sports
Production Company: The Bear
Project Type:  Social Media Campaign (will run 2 weeks)
Union Status: Non-Union
Project Rate: $250/day per family member
Shoot Date(s): January 21-23 OR 22-24, 2026 (will shoot 1 day within this range)
Shoot Location: Austin, TX. Must work local to Austin.

‚Äî
We are looking for:
[REAL FAMILY] Looking for real Latino or mixed/blended Latino families with kids who may have some soccer skills. Kids can range from 5-15 y/o. Parents can range from 30-45 y/o.

If your family might be a fit and are interested in submitting, please submit ASAP to submissions@vickyboonecasting.com by sending the following info:
*Name
*City you live in
*Contact Number
*Two recent photos of your family
*Confirm you are avail for all the dates mentioned or list conflicts (1/21-1/23, 1/22-1/24, 2026)
*Please tell us about your kid(s) soccer experience if they have any!
*Please use the subject line ‚ÄúREAL FAMILY‚Äù

We look forward to your submissions!
Team VBC

items.text:
Genre: Dark fantasy / Psychological Horror

Length: 25 - 30 minutes

Location: BERLIN 

Shooting: End of January/ Beginning of February

Budget: unpaid (graduation film)

Hey everyone, we are casting several supporting roles for a dark atmospheric graduation proof-of-concept film that blends mythology, psychological horror, and realism. This project explores power, identity, and the uncanny hidden beneath everyday life.

If you‚Äôre a fan of The Sandman, Pan‚Äôs Labrynth, and Only Lovers Left Alive, then you will feel right at home.

Actors of all backgrounds are encouraged to apply.

ROLES AVAILABLE

Spati owner (30s - 60s) - Male

A grounded ordinary presence in the mortal world. Calm and slightly detached. The Spati owner acts as an anchor to reality before things begin to unravel.

Ria (20s - 30s) - Female

Sharp, perceptive, emotionally guarded. She carries tension beneath casual conversation.

Pierre (20s - 30s) - Male

Charming on the surface but unsettling underneath. He speaks easily but holds something back.

Darius (20s - 30s) - Male

Charismatic, confident, slightly arrogant. Darius is a natural leader in social spaces. However, under pressure, his warmth slips.

Coveliat (30s) - Female

A creature of death. Uncanny, ritualistic presence, more felt than understood. Her claws can slash through the strongest of materials.

Girl 1 (20s) - Female

Social, warm, slightly obvious. She represents normality and comfort, until that comfort curdles into unease.

Girl 2 (20s -30s) - Female

More observant than girl 1. She picks up on subtle shifts in tone and energy. Friendly, but with flickers of suspicion.

IF INTERESTED

We would kindly ask you to send an email to:

celia.t@catalyst-students.com

The submission will be done in the form of self-tapes rather than in-person auditions.

The self-tape information will be sent via email.

Looking forward to hearing from you!

Bright Star Touring Theatre is currently seeking actors for our 2-person national tours. We are accepting performers from all backgrounds including Hispanic, Black, and Indigenous actors. We are casting numerous shows including: ‚ÄúAlice in Wonderland‚Äù, ‚ÄúThe Wizard of Oz‚Äù, ‚ÄúWe Can Do It: A Celebration of Women‚Äôs History‚Äù, and ‚ÄúDino Academy‚Äù, a brand new show with realistic dinosaur puppets!

This is a paid opportunity, including a compensated rehearsal period, with travel and lodging provided for the duration of the contract. There is availability from January 2026 through Spring of 2026. Compensation is set at $450/week, with a $50/week bonus upon completion of the tour.

Applicants should have professional theatre training and experience (a theatre degree is preferable), a valid driver's license, as well as a clean driving and criminal record. We are currently only accepting applicants who are 21 or older. We are looking for strong character actors who are self motivated, independent, and want to travel to exciting, new places!

Please submit your headshot, resume, and availability to casting@brightstartheatre.com to be considered. We will be conducting virtual auditions via Zoom.

Hello. I‚Äôm looking for performance and literary artists (I have enough visual artists already) who do NOT use AI in their art (other AI use is fine).  

I‚Äôm highlighting 1 new artist per week (TWO per week starting in 2026!) on my website‚Äôs new project here: http://kcmagrath.com/3x3.  This is completely free. 

If interested in participating, please EMAIL at magrathkc@gmail.com (There are no in-person meetings or phone calls; it‚Äôs  all done by email.) There, let me know what type of artist you are and send links to your work if you‚Äôre a performer, or send a few photos of your work if literary. 

If it‚Äôs a good fit, I‚Äôll send you a short list of what I‚Äôll need from you as well as your 3 questions (everyone gets different questions).

I‚Äôve completed over 80 artist highlight pages already, and spaces are limited. 

Thanks so much!

items.text:
We are casting confident, expressive individuals to appear as contestants/guests on a high-energy, unscripted talk show inspired by classic formats such as Jeremy Kyle and Jerry Springer.

The show will be hosted by massive influencer, who will take the role of the presenter, guiding conversations, mediating disputes, and attempting to resolve real or semi-scripted personal conflicts in an entertaining, fast-paced environment.

This is a performance-based role requiring strong personality, emotional range, and the ability to react naturally on camera.

Role Description ‚Äì Contestants / Guests

Selected participants will appear on the show as individuals involved in a personal conflict, relationship issue, family dispute, secret reveal, or moral dilemma. Scenarios may include (but are not limited to):

Relationship breakdowns or accusations

Love triangles or cheating allegations

Friendship or family fallouts

Hidden secrets or confrontations

Lifestyle or behavioural conflicts

You will be expected to:

Play a character or heightened version of yourself

Engage in open, confrontational, or emotionally charged discussions

React naturally to questions, accusations, and audience/chat interaction

Remain in character throughout the segment

Be comfortable with raised voices, dramatic moments, and comedic tension

Ideal Candidate

Aged 18+

Confident and expressive on camera

Comfortable with confrontation and emotional performance

Strong improvisation skills (acting experience is a plus, but not required)

Able to think quickly and respond naturally in live situations

Thick-skinned and comfortable being part of viral, high-reach content

Important Notes

This is entertainment content, not a real counselling or therapy show

Scenarios may be planned, semi-scripted, or improvised

Content will be broadcast live and clipped for social platforms (TikTok, Instagram, YouTube, etc.)

Applicants must consent to being filmed and distributed online

Compensation

Paid role

Rate dependent on role complexity, screen time, and experience

Casting-Aufruf: üé•üé¨

f√ºr unseren Kurzfilm "G√ºterbahnhof 23" suchen wir noch eine m√§nnliche Nebenrolle und Komparsen in M√ºnchen. Die ersten Szenen sind bereits abgedreht. Das Casting findet online statt. 

Was wird genau gesucht? 

Ein Sicherheitsbeamten als Kollege f√ºr die Rolle Frau Steinmetz. ( Nebenrolle ) 

Spielalter: 45-60 Jahre. Leichte Strenge. Muss etwas Druck aus√ºben k√∂nnen. 

Fahrtkosten und Unterkunft k√∂nnen leider von uns nicht √ºbernommen werden, daher sind Darsteller aus M√ºnchen und Umgebung super. Gerne auch aus anderen Bundesl√§ndern, wenn die Reise selbst √ºbernommen werden k√∂nnte.

Das ist unser erstes selbstgedrehtes Projekt, weshalb wir die Kosten ( noch ) nicht √ºbernehmen k√∂nnen.

Casting Call: üé•üé¨

For our short film "G√ºterbahnhof 23" (Freight Depot 23), we are looking for a male supporting actor and extras in Munich. The first scenes have already been filmed. The casting call will be online.

What exactly are we looking for?

A security guard to play a colleague for the character of Ms. Steinmetz. (Supporting role)

Playing age: 45-60 years. Slightly strict. Must be able to exert some pressure.

Unfortunately, we cannot cover travel and accommodation costs, so actors from Munich and the surrounding area are ideal. We are also open to actors from other German states if they can cover their own travel expenses.

**PAID** Hi everyone! We are currently casting for WISP, a haunting coming-of-age drama about isolation, queer longing, and the grip of an unseen presence.

To be Shot in: West Yorkshire.

 

Synopsis:

Sixteen-year-old Noah has spent weeks drifting from everyone he loves,

manipulated by an unseen presence. When his best friend Sam turns up on New Year‚Äôs Eve, Noah finds himself caught between feelings he‚Äôs long buried and the Voice that refuses to let him go.

 

Characters:

NOAH (16‚Äì25, male) ‚Äì Quiet, introspective, emotionally guarded. Must be able to convey internal conflict, subtle fear, and vulnerability with restraint.

SAM (16‚Äì25, male) ‚Äì Warm, intuitive, and grounded. Noah‚Äôs best friend; emotionally open, present, and deeply human.

 

Shooting: 12/2 ‚Äì 15/2   (Night Shoots)

Payment: TBD ‚Äî we are happy to discuss this with you.          

 

üì© Contact: [jaxon.s.murtagh@gmail.com](mailto:jaxon.s.murtagh@gmail.com) with Showreel if available. Script will be available.

Please feel free to share or tag anyone who might be interested.  üå≥üñ§

‚ÄúYou‚Äôre on an ocean liner on the high seas. Bad weather is threatening and the crew rushes to string a rope on the deck, the length of the ship. When the storm arrives and you‚Äôre losing your footing, what do you do? You reach for what you NEED, your goal, your objective, that‚Äôs what you reach for. It‚Äôll get you where you have to go.‚Äù 

Stella Adler as paraphrased by James Lipton.

NEW YEAR, NEW CLASS!!! 

Let‚Äôs explore the depth, boundaries, authenticity and grow the range of your acting. 

START THE YEAR INSPIRED! 

Come for a workout. NOW is the perfect time to sign up for all or any of the 3 steps our comprehensive CERTIFICATE PROGRAM! 

STEP 1: PRIVATE COACHING - 

6x1hr sessions, learn or re-enforce the essentials, with trusted process preparation techniques and direction, we prepare and tape contrasting monologues. Add to your reel! 
$499 + tx.

STEP 2: SEMIPRIVATE, SCENE-STUDY: 
3x2hr sessions. I partner you, we review and apply the preparation techniques. We tape 2 scenes with playback, notes and direction, with a focus on on-camera technique - living in the scene! Add to your reel! 
$299 + tx.
 
Or .. alternate STEP 2:  SIGN UP FOR THE JANUARY THURSDAY NIGHT SCENE-STUDY CLASS: 
JAN. 8, 15, 22, 29: 6-9 pm. 
$299 + tx. 
We‚Äôre preparing and taping scenes, telling compelling stories, applying foundational, analytical preparation techniques, with a focus on screen acting skills, using 2 cameras. 

STEP 3: THE SUCCESSFUL AUDITIONS WORKSHOP:
2 days, sharpen your audition skills, plus SELF-TAPE AUDITIONS, for commercials and film and TV series, we tape your 2 auditions, with critique, coaching, direction and demonstration. Next: FEB. 22nd & 23rd, repeats every 3rd mth. 
$199 + tx.

CERTIFICATE PROGRAM (ALL 3 STEPS):
Comprehensive training! $899 + tx. 

Add tape for your reel! Agent referrals! For prices and more information:
416 294-3754 / bongoproductions.com

Professional coaching, with Michael Caruana, at bongo productions, trusted, since 1996! www.bongoproductions.com

With 2026 right around the corner The Audition Pal are thrilled to be announcing our first 2026 workshop- and it‚Äôs a big one 

Sophie Pearson Casting will be hosting a Zoom workshop on the morning of 17th January (GMT). 

Here‚Äôs a Bio on Sophie Below:

Sophie started her career working as an associate for Ros and John Hubbard, where she worked on projects such as ‚ÄúJourney‚Äôs End‚Äù (Directed by Saul Dibb), ‚ÄòThe More You Ignore Me‚Äô (Directed by Keith English), and ‚ÄòTime of Our Lives‚Äô (Directed by Roger Goldby). She then worked at Des Hamilton Casting, where she cast noteworthy ventures like ‚ÄúHilma‚Äù (Directed by Lasse Hallstr√∂m), the Netflix sensation ‚ÄúTop Boy,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe King‚Äù (Directed by David Mich√¥d), ‚ÄúJojo Rabbit‚Äù (Directed by Taika Watiti), and ‚ÄúMy First Film‚Äù (Directed by Zia Anger). Since starting Sophie Pearson Casting, Sophie has worked on many projects including ‚ÄòVows‚Äô starring Sarah Parish and Eddie Marsan and ‚ÄòThe Man With The Urn‚Äô starring Ciaran Hinds, Olga Kurlenko and Stephen Fry. Sophie is also working alongside Dan Hubbard Casting, on projects such as the TV series ‚ÄòThe Gentleman‚Äô (directed by Guy Ritchie) and ‚ÄòThe Rage‚Äô (directed by Paul Greengrass).

We are so excited for this one! So DM us on the platform or email us at: theauditionpals@gmail.com

items.text:
**CASTING CALL**

**TITLE: ***THE LAST HIKE*
**FORMAT: **Short Film
**LOCATION: **North and West Yorkshire (on-location shoot) - exact locations TBC.
**DATES: **April (3 shoot dates)
**Expenses, travel and hot food covered, along with Associate Producer credit on film, and a handcrafted ceramic keepsake.**

**SYNOPSIS:**
*The Last Hike follows Daniel, a reserved man who reluctantly returns to his working-class roots in Yorkshire to scatter a loved one's ashes.*

*Joined by his mother, their hike through the Yorkshire Dales becomes more than just a physical journey ‚Äî it‚Äôs a path through shared memories, complicated family history and unspoken emotions.*

*Against the rugged, fading landscape of their hometown, Daniel and his mother confront the past, navigating the challenges of grief, mental health and reconciliation.*

*See our successful fundraising campaign here to learn more about the team and the project!*
[https://www.indiegogo.com/en/projects/cameronstott/the-last-hike-short-film#/section/project-story](https://www.indiegogo.com/en/projects/cameronstott/the-last-hike-short-film#/section/project-story)* *

**ROLES:**
* **DANIEL (38-45, Male)**

Emotionally reserved, sharp-edged, physically capable for hiking scenes. Must deliver restrained but intense emotional beats.

* **MUM (58-65, Female)**
Warm and expressive, with the ability to shift between lightness and emotional volatility. Strong dramatic instincts essential.

* **YOUNG DANIEL (4-7, Male) - Will also need a caregiver with them.**
Gentle, expressive child performer. Short scenes requiring natural reactions and simple physical actions.

**ACCENT:**

Yorkshire accents!

**TO APPLY:**
Please send: Full name, headshots, showreel links, filming availability for around April and the general area you‚Äôre based in to *thelasthikefilm@gmail.com*

with the subject line ‚ÄúTHE LAST HIKE ‚Äì ROLE NAME‚Äù.

items.text:
Hey!

Wir produzieren f√ºr die lokalen For-Future-Gruppen der Region T√ºbingen satirische Beitr√§ge, die an "Die Anstalt" (ZDF) angelehnt sind und haben deswegen noch einige Rollen zu besetzen.

Kurzum versucht Mutter Natur in einem fiktiven Gerichtsraum gegen Friedrich Merz das Recht zu erstreiten, endlich als juristische Person wahrgenommen zu werden. Dabei helfen ihr Zeugen wie "Die Psyche der Menschen", "Der Vorgarten" und "Der Begradigte Fluss". Da das Format nicht nur satirisch-humoristisch ist, sondern auch einen informativen Charakter hat, wird das Projekt sehr dialoglastig sein. 

üìçWir drehen in T√ºbingen. 

üïû Geplant sind 1-2 Drehtage im Zeitraum Anfang bis Ende Februar 2026 (genauere Informationen folgen)

üé¨ Logline: In ihrem Ziel, das erste Mal als juristisches Subjekt wahrgenommen zu werden kommt es zu einer Konfrontation mit Friedrich Merz. 

üíµ Wir sind eine No-Budget-Produktion, weshalb wir leider keine keine Gagen vergeben k√∂nnen.

Anbei ist unsere Projektmappe und Moodboard, die Rollen sind dort noch mal ausf√ºhrlich beschrieben. 

Schreibt uns bei Interesse eine E-mail, in der ihr euch kurz vorstellt - wir melden uns dann zur√ºck!

im.namen.der.natur@gmail.com

Wir freuen uns!

Liebe Gr√º√üe,
Devid

* Comfortable working on an independent short film set

* (Optional) Demo reel or self-tape

CASTING CALL - Vancouver, BC 

Zariya, a 20 something from a small town. She embodies the duality of light and dark femininity, delicate yet strong. She has long dark hair and darker features. She is represented by the Sun card in Tarot. She is the light within the dark, a beacon of hope. 

Title: The Burden of Transformation

Writer/Director: Salom√© Mu√±oz 

Genre: Drama

Themes: Psychological, Dreamy, Comedy within a Tragedy

Shooting dates: January 20/21 2026

You receive: copy, credit and meal! 

This project is very theatrical and over the top, a background in theatre performance/stage acting is ideal but not required. 

If you are interested, please send me headshots and a resume via [s.munoz@infocusfilmschool.com](mailto:s.munoz@infocusfilmschool.com) and for more information look to @theburdenoftransformation on instagram! 

Thank you!

items.text:
## **CASTING CALL ‚Äì ‚ÄúTETRACHROMACY‚Äù (Short Film)**

**Project Title:** *Tetrachromacy*

**Genre:** Drama

**Location:** Vancouver, BC

**Shoot Dates:** December 29 & 30, 2025

**Compensation:** Indie film, great experience, Volunteer project (we are all volunteers, there‚Äôs no budget.)

Synopsis

*Tetrachromacy* follows **Nathan**, a photojournalist who loses his ability to see color after a head injury, leaving his world in stark black and white. One year later, he discovers that color returns only through AI-recreated images of his photographs. His life shifts when he encounters **Claire**, a woman in a yellow dress who appears vividly in color within his monochromatic reality, challenging his isolation and reshaping his sense of connection.

Role breakdown
NATHAN(Lead, 30s, male)

* A passionate photojournalist with a strong artistic eye
* Suffers from cerebral achromatopsia following a head injury
* Intelligent, introspective, emotionally reserved
* Slightly awkward when expressing feelings
* **Emotional arc:** moves from isolation and frustration toward wonder, openness, and human connection

**Notes:**

This is a subtle, performance-driven role. Actor must be comfortable conveying emotion through restraint, stillness, and internal conflict.

Submission Details

Please submit:
* Headshot
* Resume (or relevant acting experience)
* Demo reel (if available)
* A short Self-tape

**Submit to:** [s6films.co@gmail.com](mailto:s6films.co@gmail.com)

**Submission Deadline:** December 21, 2025

If selected auditions will be hosted on December 22, 2025

Who we are:

S6 films is a a group of passionate filmmakers pursuing creating films we care about amidst busy life and jobs in video production.

items.text:
**Perfect Xmas Gift for Actors! *****‚ÄúTHE ACTOR'S MANIFESTO: Create a Successful Acting Career‚Äù*** Amazon Books--blends techniques, neuroscience, psychology, and industry business savvy to help actors master the craft and the industry.

**What it covers:**

The Craft: Deep dives into realism in acting, key techniques and modern approaches.

The Psyche: Strategies for managing an actor's mental state.

The Business: Advice on navigating the entertainment industry.

Science: Neuroscience on how acting works in the brain.

Holistic Approach: Skill, mental health, and business acumen.

 

Written by Linda Ann Watt, SAG-AFTRA, AEA Member, SAG-AFTRA Signatory Producer/Director, MFA in Theatre Pedagogy, and 2015 Tony Award Nominee for Education. This book bridges theory and the demands of an acting career. **TheActorsManifesto.org**

Location: Los Angeles !

We‚Äôre looking for an actress with presence, energy, and confidence to appear in 2‚Äì3 minute skits designed for fast-paced, attention-grabbing content.

If you‚Äôre comfortable on camera, can deliver strong emotion, and know how to keep viewers locked in from start to finish ‚Äî this is for you.

What You‚Äôll Be Doing:

üé¨ Performing short, scripted or semi-scripted skits

‚ö° Delivering high energy, clear expression, and strong engagement

üé• Creating content that feels real, sharp, and impactful

Pay & Perks:

üíµ $25/hour

üí∏ Performance bonuses available

üìà Potential for steady, ongoing work

You‚Äôre a Strong Fit If You:

 ‚Ä¢ Bring high energy and confidence on camera

 ‚Ä¢ Can switch emotions quickly and stay engaging

 ‚Ä¢ Are reliable, punctual, and professional

 ‚Ä¢ Want consistent work and growth opportunities

Experience:

Acting experience is a plus, but camera confidence and energy matter most.

Environment:

Fast-moving, creative, and focused. We value effort, presence, and consistency.

üì© How to Apply:

Send a short intro or a headshot and DM!!!

If you can own the screen for 2‚Äì3 minutes, we want to work with you. üî•üé•

items.text:
Hello!

Currently at the start of the casting process for the workshop version of my show next September!

(including 2 presentation milestones in February and June - more production details upon invite)

If you are a queer identifying musical theatre performer and feel aligned with the piece I would love to have you!

PS. Please note this is a university funded production and due to guidelines I am not allowed to pay anyone for their time. Please keep this in mind if you are thinking of applying and know that your time and energy will be deeply appreciated in other ways. Hoping for this to be only the beginning!

Loooove,

Chris xx

items.text:
**CASTING CALL!!!**

We are casting for a new tour of the children‚Äôs theatre show, ‚ÄúTom Gates Live‚Äù, based on the popular book series by Liz Pichon.

The show is written and directed by Miranda Larson with songs and music by Barrie Bignold and is produced by Mark Thompson at MT Productions.

Rehearsals begin on 19th January ‚Äì 29th January 2025 in London.
Tour dates Jan ‚Äì Oct 2026. We are currently have 65 tour dates and counting.
**ROLE: Tom Gates**

Tom Gates is an easily distracted and creative 10-year-old boy who loves doodling, listening to music, and annoying his older sister, Delia.

He is best friends with Derek, and they share a passion for music, with dreams of becoming rock stars in their band, DogZombies.

We are looking for a musical theatre performer that can sing, perform slapstick and comedy, and can perform the role of a young boy.

Within the show, there is basic singing, dancing and movement but nothing too technical.

The successful applicant will need to be comfortable assisting with the load ins/ outs and have a full UK drivers licence as they will be asked to assist driving the touring van

Playing age: 16 years - 23 years

Gender: Male

**Contract info:**

Rehearsal fee: ¬£550pw

Show day fee: ¬£150

Travel day fee: ¬£50

Subsistence: ¬£20

Please send cv's and headshots to *casting.mtproductions@gmail.com*

We‚Äôd like to share an official **casting opportunity** from **Bor Productions** aboard **MSC Cruise Lines**. This casting is not hosted by Evoque ‚Äî we are passing on the details so performers can apply.

**Casting Needs:**
**Male Singers (MS1/MS2)** ‚Äî tenor and high baritone roles with contemporary repertoire; some MS1 roles require basic rap performance.
**Male Singer/Dancer** ‚Äî production choreography and strong vocals for certain MSC ships

**Contract Info & Requirements:**
‚Ä¢ STCW certification (or willingness to obtain)
‚Ä¢ Seafarers medical (ENG1 equivalent or MSC PEME)
‚Ä¢ Required vaccinations (Yellow Fever, MMR, Varicella)
‚Ä¢ Seaman‚Äôs book for Panama‚Äëregistered vessels
‚Ä¢ Contract durations typically 5‚Äì8 months

If you‚Äôre an experienced performer seeking international cruise opportunities, find more details and submit your application at **EvoqueHub.com** or by emailing your materials to **[auditions@evoquehub.com](mailto:auditions@evoquehub.com)**.

items.text:
STUDENT SHORT FILM CASTING 

Shooting dates: 23rd-25th January

Location: Vancouver, North Vancouver

Volunteer, lunch and copy of film provided. 

**MARTY (20-25)**
* A young pianist struggling with anxiety and health issues. His passion for music is strong, but he is haunted by self-doubt and physical limitations. Emotionally vulnerable, he carries the weight of the past, yet despite the toll on his body and mind, he persists in pursuing his dreams.

**MARTY'S MOTHER (40s-50s)**
* A supportive, hard-working single mother. Cares deeply for her son and masks her worries about his skill with a calm, composed demeanor, despite the mental and physical toll it‚Äôs taking on her.

**SUBMISSION**

Please send:
* Headshot or recent photo
* Short bio or acting resume (if available)

Shortlisted candidates will be invited to an audition, January 7th. If unavailable, a self-tape will be accepted. 

**Submit to:** melodymovie2026@gmail.com

With 2026 right around the corner The Audition Pal are thrilled to be announcing our first 2026 workshop- and it‚Äôs a big one 

Sophie Pearson Casting will be hosting a Zoom workshop on the morning of 17th January (GMT). 

Here‚Äôs a Bio on Sophie Below:

Sophie started her career working as an associate for Ros and John Hubbard, where she worked on projects such as ‚ÄúJourney‚Äôs End‚Äù (Directed by Saul Dibb), ‚ÄòThe More You Ignore Me‚Äô (Directed by Keith English), and ‚ÄòTime of Our Lives‚Äô (Directed by Roger Goldby). She then worked at Des Hamilton Casting, where she cast noteworthy ventures like ‚ÄúHilma‚Äù (Directed by Lasse Hallstr√∂m), the Netflix sensation ‚ÄúTop Boy,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe King‚Äù (Directed by David Mich√¥d), ‚ÄúJojo Rabbit‚Äù (Directed by Taika Watiti), and ‚ÄúMy First Film‚Äù (Directed by Zia Anger). Since starting Sophie Pearson Casting, Sophie has worked on many projects including ‚ÄòVows‚Äô starring Sarah Parish and Eddie Marsan and ‚ÄòThe Man With The Urn‚Äô starring Ciaran Hinds, Olga Kurlenko and Stephen Fry. Sophie is also working alongside Dan Hubbard Casting, on projects such as the TV series ‚ÄòThe Gentleman‚Äô (directed by Guy Ritchie) and ‚ÄòThe Rage‚Äô (directed by Paul Greengrass).

We are so excited for this one! So DM us on the platform or email us at: theauditionpals@gmail.com

Monday, January 5, and Tuesday, January 6 at @ 7:00pm
Callback by invitation on Wednesday January 7 @ 7pm

Play Overview:
A fast-paced, heightened comedic farce set in 1923 England. Infidelity, mistaken identities, exaggerated manners, and bold physical comedy drive the show. All roles require strong comedic timing, physicality, and the ability to deliver heightened, crisp dialogue in a British dialect.

The director encourages diverse casting. No role has a strict requirement of ethnicity or race.

Physicality & Intimacy: Farcical timing, comedic blocking, and in some roles intimacy scenes (kissing / romantic chemistry) are required; also comedic violence or slapstick may appear.

As the play is set in 1923 England: RP / British accent is required.

Character Breakdown:
Sylvia
Gender: Female
Age: Mid-20s to 40s
Description: A ‚Äúlovely and rash romantic.‚Äù Sylvia is impulsive, passionate, and clings to romantic idealism. She‚Äôs the one who initiates the comedic uproar by deciding to reveal her affair which triggers the farcical unraveling of secrets.
Physical / Performance Notes: Should embody flirtatious charm, emotional volatility, and physical energy. Expect moments of passion/intimacy (kissing or romantic touch) and heightened comedic reactions or slapstick. 

Beau
Gender: Male
Age: Mid-20s to late 40s
Description: Beau is described as ‚Äúperhaps the best-looking man in Britain.‚Äù He‚Äôs charming, handsome, and somewhat complacent. A man comfortable with the status quo, even when his romantic life is scandalous. His affair with Sylvia is marked by both desire and hesitation.
Physical / Performance Notes: Should have presence, charm, and ease. Needs comfort with intimacy (romantic scenes) and comedic timing, especially with farcical elements. RP British accent.

Marjorie
Gender: Female
Age: Mid-20s to 40s (she is very pregnant in the play)
Description: Beau‚Äôs wife. ‚ÄúEight months pregnant, pragmatic‚Äù, grounded, and composed, even in the face of shocking revelations. Underneath, she has a sharp edge; she‚Äôs ‚Äúa tad spicy.‚Äù 
Physical / Performance Notes: You will be wearing an insanely pregnant-belly. Needs emotional range: from shock to self preservation to possible betrayal or strength. Comedic instincts + ability to react strongly to chaos.

Clarke
Gender: Male
Age: Mid-20s to late 40s
Description: Sylvia‚Äôs husband. A refined, ‚Äúdistinguished gent with a lover‚Äôs spirit.‚Äù He may appear respectable and stable, but underneath, his loyalties and feelings are complicated. Entangled in the web of affairs and deceptions.
Physical / Performance Notes: Needs a balance of dignity and vulnerability. Believable as a gentleman, but also capable of comedic panic or confusion. Comfortable with farce pacing and quick reaction work. 

Dierdre
Gender: Female
Age: Early 20s to 30s (or thereabouts, though exact age is flexible)
Description: She‚Äôs described in the script as ‚Äúan awfully pretty, sometimes wise, nincompoop.‚Äù She‚Äôs na√Øve, sweet, perhaps a bit ditzy, but also occasionally offers piercing insight. She often reacts to the chaos with bewilderment and innocence, which amplifies the comedy.
Physical / Performance Notes: Needs to deliver endearing innocence, comedic timing, and willingness to play ‚Äúditzy‚Äù with heart. Should be comfortable with exaggerated reactions, physical comedy and the heightened energy of farce. 

Richard
Gender: Male
Age: 30s to 50s
Description: A dark comedic twist in the farce. Richard is described as ‚Äúmurderous‚Äù but ‚Äúgentle,‚Äù meaning he occupies the role of destabilizing danger amidst the comedic chaos. His arrival triggers tension, threat, and unexpected comedy. A perfect blend of menace and absurdity.
Physical / Performance Notes: Should be able to handle heightened dramatic tension and farcical comedy. Perhaps a little brooding, but also capable of shambling comedy or over-the-top melodrama. Must be okay with comedic threat, possibly physical acting (gun or
threat).

Bring a headshot and resume and be ready to list ALL conflicts.

Performances: February 27 to March 22, 2026
Rehearsals Begin January 12 at Cabrillo Playhouse
All genders, body types, and ethnicities are encouraged to audition
There is a small stipend offered

12/12/25

(This Is My) Family (Short Film)

A Comedy about family dynamics

A family near breaking point, implodes in one night. 

Shooting April location TBC

Auditioning: We want to receive self tapes first and those who make it to the next stage, we would love in person auditions by late January of 2026. 

Travel Expenses paid

Student film being screened at The BFI and will be entered into film festivals

Elizabeth (50s-60s) - Narcissistic mother who dominates her kids' lives. She speaks her mind much to the reluctance of everyone around her..

Marie (30s-40s) - She‚Äôs in the middle of a mid-life crisis and she blames elizabeth as she thinks she‚Äôs not the perfect mother that she presents herself as. So Marie rebels against this supposed ‚Äòperfect family‚Äô.

Shaun (30-40s) - Shaun simply accepts his place in the world and has very little self respect. He is in a loveless relationship with his wife (Claire) however he does not rebel against her out of fear of living life alone in his 40s. Yet again every man has his breaking point. 

Clare (30s-40s) - Clare needs power and control, so she has found a man she can excerpt this power on (Shaun.) Clare and Elizabeth are very similar and therefore team up to inflate each other's egos at the expense of Marie and Shaun. 

Email: tylerbrownework@gmail.com for further details

Please only respond if you are based in England as our budget will not cover travel from abroad.

URGENT-

Looking for a couple of performers available 23rd & 24th December in the Herts/Beds/Bucks area. Both dates 10am-4pm.

Non-speaking elf role, super silly and fun, physical improv lead. You will be working in a pair travelling to several different locations throughout the day. The other elf can drive so as long as you can get to a meeting point, driving isn't necessarily needed. 

Costume provided, no accommodation (looking for local people). Would suit students home for Christmas with an interest in acting and performance, and a whole lot of Christmas cheer! 

Pop me a message for further info ASAP. ‚ù§Ô∏è

items.text:
This is the casting call for my short film, Metalhead, its a project that I'm very passionate about and my hope is that you may be to.

Filming in stoke in January.

This is my 5th filmmaking project, and I really would like to take this opportunity to push the envelope when it comes to working with actors and drawing out performances.

If either of these roles stand out as a role that would suit you, please don't hesitate to get in touch at cian4472@hotmail.co.uk

VOLUNTEER ONLY

This is a student production, and unfortunately I don't have the budget to be able to pay crew or cast. I am more than happy to pay for expenses and catering for contributors.

This is the casting call for my short film, Metalhead, its a project that I'm very passionate about and my hope is that you may be to.

Filming in stoke in January.

This is my 5th filmmaking project, and I really would like to take this opportunity to push the envelope when it comes to working with actors and drawing out performances.

If either of these roles stand out as a role that would suit you, please don't hesitate to get in touch at cian4472@hotmail.co.uk

VOLUNTEER ONLY

This is a student production, and unfortunately I don't have the budget to be able to pay crew or cast. I am more than happy to pay for expenses and catering for contributors.

ROLE DETAILS

 ‚Ä¢ Gender: Male

 ‚Ä¢ Ethnicity: Black

 ‚Ä¢ Age Range: 30‚Äì40

 ‚Ä¢ Union Status: Non-Union

 ‚Ä¢ Compensation: Unpaid (indie project)

CHARACTER DESCRIPTION

This is not a stereotypical tough or cold detective.

We‚Äôre looking for a detective who leads with empathy, curiosity, and human understanding ‚Äî someone who listens more than he interrogates. A man who sees people as people first, not just cases. Calm, grounded, emotionally intelligent, and present.

The character plays an important role in shaping the emotional tone of the story.

ABOUT THE PROJECT

ANXIETY is an independent short film with strong psychological and emotional themes, with potential for future expansion. This project is passion-driven and focused on authentic performances and meaningful storytelling.

üì© SUBMISSIONS

Please send the following to:

anxietyfeaturefilm@gmail.com

 ‚Ä¢ Headshot

 ‚Ä¢ Resume (if available)

 ‚Ä¢ Reel or self-tape (optional)

items.text:
Marketing Macabre - a horror public relations company created to give independent filmmakers an affordable alternative. We focus on the importance of publicity to gain momentum and we work with some of the biggest genre websites in the world. Our mission is to get your project in front of your audience, the horror public - the most devoted fan base in all of entertainment.   

Our enhanced filmmaker services will supply you with everything needed on your cinematic journey from pre-production to post-production to distribution.  We have forged relationships out of trust and loyalty with partners that stretch from Hollywood studios to distribution companies.   In the evolution of horror, we have evolved from a marketing company to something more.  

A creation born out of necessity and a genesis into a one-stop-horror-shop that offers not only marketing, but opportunities in brand development, film funding, and distribution.  There are many complexities of making a feature film but our marketing militia will guide you on your journey and be your source to access the horror multiverse that is Marketing Macabre.

items.text:
I recently had a detailed conversation with Kurt Evans of Artist2Artist, one of the established actor showcase platforms, specifically around demo reels, self-tapes, and how casting actually encounters actors.

A few points from that discussion are worth sharing, because they clarify a lot of confusion I keep seeing among actors at different stages.

On demo reels:
Casting directors are not ignoring traditional demo reels. A professional demo reel is still exactly that ‚Äî the professional work you‚Äôve done, compiled into a roughly three-minute video. What matters is how that reel is structured.

Rather than one or two long scenes, the reel works best when it‚Äôs made up of multiple 20‚Äì30 second sections, each clearly showing a type you would naturally be called in for ‚Äî parent, authority figure, professional roles, etc. The goal isn‚Äôt to replace the reel, but to make it immediately readable. Realistically, a director may only watch about 20 seconds before deciding whether you fit, so clarity matters more than length.

On highly produced self-tapes:
We spoke about the rise of very cinematic, highly produced self-tapes ‚Äî essentially mini-movies. Kurt isn‚Äôt against production value. In fact, he shared an example where one panelist loved a highly edited tape, while another felt it looked more like a finished production than an audition.

The key point he emphasized is that the purpose of a self-tape or showcase submission is still to evaluate acting. Most actors audition two to three times a week. It‚Äôs neither realistic nor necessary to shoot a short film every time. What casting needs is a clear window into the performance. Overproduction isn‚Äôt a mistake ‚Äî it‚Äôs just not what casting is primarily judging.

On agents and casting access:
This is the part many actors misunderstand. Casting primarily encounters actors through agents. It‚Äôs not about gatekeeping or access ‚Äî it‚Äôs how the system functions. There‚Äôs a trust relationship between agents and casting offices.

In a traditional setting, a casting assistant may block off hours of time, receive hundreds of short submissions from agents, and narrow those down to about twenty strong fits. That‚Äôs how casting begins to connect with talent. Without representation, casting offices often have no way of knowing an actor exists.

What showcases like Artist2Artist aim to do is create a space where casting can watch actors work outside the volume and time pressure of the standard submission pipeline.

The takeaway from the conversation was straightforward:
For actors who want to be seen consistently in film and television, representation is the first gateway into that ecosystem.

## christmas time at The Three Crutches, 
##                       A traditional family-friendly pub

Ditzy, Sparkle and Tiny spread the Christmas cheer and Santa descended to The Three Crutches today. 

Located on the outskirts of Cobham woods on the scenic drive into Higham village, The Three Crutches provides a cosy respite from exploring the village and surrounding natural landscape. With local walks starting from our doorstep into the picturesque countryside, a welcome haven after a day exploring so sit back, relax and indulge in delicious food with your favourite drink in hand.

Merry Christmas everyone!

items.text:
Warmest Holiday Wishes from Our Creative Family to Yours!

As the season blankets Colorado and 2025 draws to a close, we at S.E.B. Casting, CSA want to take a moment to thank you for being part of our vibrant community of performers, directors, producers, advertisers, agents and creative visionaries. Your talent and passion continue to inspire us every day.

A Year of Breakthrough Performances
2025 has been extraordinary for the S.E.B. Casting community. From launching careers in award-winning productions to connecting diverse talent with innovative projects, we've watched with pride as performers have shined in everything from national commercials and viral ad campaigns to feature length films. Your commitment to authentic storytelling has helped productions across Colorado and beyond create more inclusive, powerful productions.

What's New at S.E.B.
We're thrilled to announce our studio expansion will be complete in January 2026! This means a more comofrtable audition space, improved casting facilities, and a dedicated area for talent and production. Plus, our Commitment to the Community will continue to grow, lifting individuals, groups. organizations and our whole state as a vibrant, positive, engaging, equitable hub for media arts and artists. 

Holiday Self-Care for Performers:
The holidays can be both magical and hectic for creative professionals. Here are our top tips to stay centered and ready for opportunities in the new year:

Schedule downtime: Block specific days for complete rest - no auditions, no rehearsals, no networking

Stay vocally healthy: Maintain your instrument with extra hydration and vocal rest during holiday gatherings

Update materials: Use the quiet period between December 20-January 5 to refresh headshots, reels, and resumes

Connect authentically: Attend industry gatherings not just for networking, but to genuinely celebrate the season with your creative community 

Here's to New Beginnings!
As we wrap up 2025, we're filled with gratitude for this remarkable community. The new year promises exciting productions, fresh opportunities, and continued growth for Colorado's vibrant media arts scene. Whether you're a seasoned professional or just beginning your journey, know that S.E.B. Casting, CSA is here to champion your unique voice and talent.

**Perfect Xmas Gift for Actors! *****‚ÄúTHE ACTOR'S MANIFESTO: Create a Successful Acting Career‚Äù*** Amazon Books--blends techniques, neuroscience, psychology, and industry business savvy to help actors master the craft and the industry in USA.

**What it covers:**

The Craft: Deep dives into realism in acting, key techniques and modern approaches.

The Psyche: Strategies for managing an actor's mental state.

The Business: Advice on navigating the entertainment industry.

Science: Neuroscience on how acting works in the brain.

Holistic Approach: Skill, mental health, and business acumen.

 

Written by Linda Ann Watt, SAG-AFTRA, AEA Member, SAG-AFTRA Signatory Producer/Director, MFA in Theatre Pedagogy, and 2015 Tony Award Nominee for Education. This book bridges theory and the demands of an acting career. **TheActorsManifesto.org**
